The Telegraph - Calcutta : Opinion
		 Monday, December 16, 2002 				 Babudom burden a professional hazard
								Amit Sarkar: We find that health policies are formulated by bureaucrats but executed by doctors, who have to face all sorts of trouble. How can this be overcome?																																																													It is true that our health policies are framed by bureaucrats and politicians but doctors have to execute them. They treat it as a professional hazard.
